President Biden has announced his intent to nominate several individuals for key positions in his administration. Carlos Felipe Uriarte has been nominated for Assistant Attorney General for Legislative Affairs at the U.S. Department of Justice. Uriarte currently serves as Vice President, Regulatory Counsel at Unite Us and has previous experience in various positions in government, including serving in the Obama-Biden Administration.

Gerald H. Acker has been nominated for Commissioner & Chair of the International Joint Commission. Acker is an attorney with extensive experience in law and policy in Michigan. He co-founded and manages a law firm that specializes in dispute resolutions between individuals and insurance companies.

Annie Caputo has been nominated for the Nuclear Regulatory Commission. Caputo has previous experience as a professional staff member on the U.S. Senate Armed Services Committee and served as a Commissioner of the U.S. Nuclear Regulatory Commission. She has also worked in positions related to nuclear energy and government affairs.

Bradley R. Crowell has been nominated for the Nuclear Regulatory Commission. Crowell currently serves as Director of the Nevada Department of Conservation and Natural Resources and has over 20 years of experience in energy, environment, natural resources, climate change, and national security. He has also worked in the Obama-Biden Administration at the U.S. Department of Energy.